article:
The 'Skate Canada International' is an international, senior-level invitation-
only figure skating competition organized by Skate Canada. It is the second
competition of the ISU Grand Prix of Figure Skating. The location changes
yearly. Medals are awarded in four disciplines: Ladies' singles, Men's singles,
Pair skating, and Ice dancing. The first Skate Canada was held in 1973. The 1987
competition in Calgary, Alberta was the test event for the 1988 Winter Olympic
Games. It was added to the Grand Prix series in 1995, the year the series began.

It has had different title sponsors over the years. On August 30, 2006, Skate
Canada announced a new title sponsor for Skate Canada International. Until 2010,
it will officially be the HomeSense Skate Canada International. [http://www-
.skatecanada.ca/en/news_views/press_room/news_releases/2006/aug30.cfm Skate
Canada: News & Views: Press Room ]
